# =============================================================================
# Macena CS2 Analyzer — Top-Level Production Dependencies
# =============================================================================
#
# This is the TOP-LEVEL manifest. Compile to a hashed lockfile via:
#
#   uv pip compile --generate-hashes \
#       --output-file requirements-lock.txt \
#       --extra-index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu121 \
#       requirements.in
#
# CPU-only variant:
#
#   uv pip compile --generate-hashes \
#       --output-file requirements-lock-cpu.txt \
#       --extra-index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu \
#       requirements.in
#
# Then install with `pip install --require-hashes -r requirements-lock-cpu.txt`
# (or the matching CUDA lockfile in production).
#
# Verification:  python tools/verify_lock_hashes.py
#
# Discipline (POL-DEPS-01):
# - Every dependency exact-pinned with `==`.
# - Range pins (e.g., torch>=2.1.0,<3.0) require an inline `# SEC: justified`
#   comment with the reason.
# - Phase 1 keeps these synchronised with requirements.txt; Phase 2 makes
#   requirements.txt obsolete in favour of this file + the lockfile.
#
# Doctrine §53 — Software Supply Chain Is the Core Asset.
# =============================================================================

